{
  "local_port": 42472,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are the best available social media analytics tool?",
  "response": "As of 2023, there are several powerful social media analytics tools available, each catering to different needs, platforms, and budgets. Here are some of the best social media analytics tools:\n\n### 1. **Hootsuite**\n   - **Best for**: All-in-one social media management and analytics.\n   - **Key Features**: \n     - Tracks performance across multiple platforms (Facebook, Instagram, Twitter, LinkedIn, etc.).\n     - Provides detailed reports on engagement, audience growth, and campaign performance.\n     - Offers scheduling and content management features.\n   - **Pricing**: Free plan available; paid plans start at $99/month.\n\n### 2. **Sprout Social**\n   - **Best for**: Comprehensive analytics and engagement tools.\n   - **Key Features**:\n     - Advanced analytics for Instagram, Facebook, Twitter, LinkedIn, and Pinterest.\n     - Audience demographic data and sentiment analysis.\n     - Customizable reports and dashboards.\n   - **Pricing**: Starts at $249/month (billed annually).\n\n### 3. **Buffer**\n   - **Best for**: Small businesses and individuals looking for simplicity.\n   - **Key Features**:\n     - Tracks engagement, reach, and impressions for Instagram, Facebook, Twitter, and LinkedIn.\n     - Offers post-scheduling and content planning.\n     - Easy-to-use interface with basic analytics.\n   - **Pricing**: Free plan available; paid plans start at $6/month.\n\n### 4. **Brandwatch**\n   - **Best for**: Advanced social listening and analytics.\n   - **Key Features**:\n     - Monitors brand mentions and sentiment across social media and the web.\n     - Provides deep insights into audience behavior and trends.\n     - AI-powered analytics for predictive insights.\n   - **Pricing**: Custom pricing based on needs.\n\n### 5. **Later**\n   - **Best for**: Instagram-focused analytics and scheduling.\n   - **Key Features**:\n     - Tracks Instagram performance, including story views, followers, and engagement.\n     - Provides hashtag analytics and best times to post.\n     - Offers scheduling and content planning for Instagram, Facebook, Twitter, and Pinterest.\n   - **Pricing**: Free plan available; paid plans start at $18/month.\n\n### 6. **Agorapulse**\n   - **Best for**: Team collaboration and reporting.\n   - **Key Features**:\n     - Tracks engagement, audience growth, and campaign performance across multiple platforms.\n     - Offers social listening and competitor analysis.\n     - Provides customizable reports and team collaboration tools.\n   - **Pricing**: Starts at $49/month (billed annually).\n\n### 7. **Google Analytics**\n   - **Best for**: Tracking social media traffic and conversions on websites.\n   - **Key Features**:\n     - Tracks social media referrals and user behavior on your website.\n     - Provides insights into conversions and ROI from social media campaigns.\n     - Integrates with other Google tools like Google Ads and Google Search Console.\n   - **Pricing**: Free.\n\n### 8. **Socialbakers**\n   - **Best for**: AI-driven social media marketing and analytics.\n   - **Key Features**:\n     - Tracks performance across Facebook, Instagram, Twitter, YouTube, and LinkedIn.\n     - Provides AI-driven insights and recommendations.\n     - Offers competitor benchmarking and audience analysis.\n   - **Pricing**: Custom pricing based on needs.\n\n### 9. **BuzzSumo**\n   - **Best for**: Content performance analysis and influencer identification.\n   - **Key Features**:\n     - Tracks content performance and engagement across social media.\n     - Identifies trending topics and influencers in your niche.\n     - Provides competitor analysis and content alerts.\n   - **Pricing**: Starts at $99/month.\n\n### 10. **Zoho Social**\n   - **Best for**: Zoho ecosystem users and small businesses.\n   - **Key Features**:\n     - Tracks engagement, followers, and reach across multiple platforms.\n     - Provides post scheduling and team collaboration features.\n     - Integrates with other Zoho apps and Google Analytics.\n   - **Pricing**: Starts at $10/month (billed annually).\n\n### Key Considerations When Choosing a Tool:\n- **Platforms Supported**: Ensure the tool supports the social media platforms you use.\n- **Features**: Look for features like sentiment analysis, competitor benchmarking, and custom reporting.\n- **Ease of Use**: Choose a tool with an interface that matches your skill level.\n- **Budget**: Consider the cost and whether the tool offers a free plan or trial.\n\nDepending on your specific needs\u2014whether it's in-depth analytics, social listening, or content scheduling\u2014there's a tool out there that can help you maximize your social media strategy.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
